A man has been charged with raping a 10-year-old boy in Kayole. Samuel Nahashon, who runs a movie shop at Pajil Investments, is accused of committing the offence on November 15 with another man not before court.He faces an alternative charge of indecently touching the boy without his consent.The court heard that the boy and his friends had gone to watch movies when Nahashon chased them and pulled him into a room. He then ordered the boy to bathe as punishment.Police said he refused and after half an hour, Nahashon went into the room and defiled him. He warned the boy not to tell anyone what happened.A child who was with the victim reported to his mother. Nahashon denied the charges and was set free on Sh300,000 surety bond . The mention was set for December 19.